senselogic.sitevision.api.node

Interface NodeTypeUtil

  • All Superinterfaces:
    VelocityAccess.NodeTypeUtilConstants

    @Requireable(value="NodeTypeUtil")
public interface NodeTypeUtil
extends VelocityAccess.NodeTypeUtilConstants
    Node type utility interface.

    This interface contains the primary node type names for Sitevision nodes and convenience methods for checking if a node is of a specific type.

    Tip! If you write your code in Velocity, you might want to ensure that the object actually are a Node before you execute methods in this interface. Use InstanceTypeUtil.isNode(Object) to do that.

    An instance of the Sitevision class implementing this interface can be obtained via Utils.getNodeTypeUtil(). See Utils for how to obtain an instance of the Utils interface.

    Since:
    Sitevision 2.6.2

      • isSystemUser

        boolean isSystemUser(Node aNode)
        Checks if a node is a sv:systemUser.

        Note that there are several build-in "system users" in Sitevision:

        • The System user
        • The Anonymous user (i.e. non-authenticated user)
        • The Indexer user (i.e. the user that index data in Sitevision)
        • The Validator user (i.e. the user that validates page-nodes in Sitevision)
        • The Extractor user (i.e. default "Web archive" user)
        • The Anonymized user (i.e. an anonymized user)

        Tip! Use the SystemUserUtil utility to check if a user is a specific build-in system user.

        Parameters:
        aNode - the node to be checked
        Returns:
        whether aNode is a sv:systemUser or not.
        Since:
        Sitevision 10.2
        See Also:
        isAnyUserType(Node)
